article.headline: Youngstown State 70, Lock Haven 36
article.story: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio (AP) -- Keston Roberts scored 22 points and had eight rebounds to lead Youngstown State to a 70-36 win over Division II Lock Haven on Tuesday. Quin Humphrey added 15 points and Jack Liles had 10 points and seven rebounds for the Penguins (3-6), who snapped a four-game losing streak and held an opponent to its lowest point total in 36 years. Billy Arre, who scored 13 points, was the only one of six scorers for Lock Haven (1-7) to reach double digits. Jeff Eveillard had six rebounds. Youngstown State took a 36-20 lead at halftime and outrebounded the Bald Eagles 42-27. The Penguins also scored 28 points off 23 Lock Haven turnovers. Youngstown State shot 45 percent (29-of-64), while holding the Bald Eagles to 36 percent (16-of-44). The Bald Eagles' 36 points were the fewest against the Penguins since Hiram scored 35 in December 1970.
